Five ANC Youth League members appeared in the Mthatha Magistrate s Court this week on charges relating to the assault of South African Students Congress (Sasco) members at the Walter Sisulu University s Mthatha campus. Regional National Prosecuting Authority spokesman Luxolo Tyali said the students were between the ages of 22 and 25.They face charges of assault with intent to do grievous bodily harm and made a brief appearance in court. The case was postponed to May 3.The youth league members have been identified as: Mvuyisi Tshangela, Azola Mziwendoda, Sandile Godlimpi, Enkosi Ngwadla and ANCYL chairman at the Nelson Mandela Drive site Zuko Mpika.Their arrests on Wednesday came after one of their alleged victims opened a case with police.The two ANC-aligned organisations are at loggerheads over which should have control at the Mthatha campus. Share this story: Click to share on Twitter (Opens in new window) Click to share on Facebook (Opens in new window) Click to share on LinkedIn (Opens in new window) Click to share on Tumblr (Opens in new window) Click to share on Google+ (Opens in new window) Click to share on WhatsApp (Opens in new window) Click to share on Pinterest (Opens in new window) Click to share on Reddit (Opens in new window) Click to email this to a friend (Opens in new window) Click to print (Opens in new window) Recommended Sasco defeats Daso to regain control at UFH ANC ban on student elections Where to from here for Jacob Zuma? ANC s final opportunity to grasp the revolution